"Adam Curtis is making some of the most interesting TV right now – we've always loved his work. We've gotten to know him a little over the past ten years or so, and met for pints a few times… He always refers to his ""inner DJ"", which is evident on all his films - the song selection is always incredible. Throughout our time doing God Colony we've always looked for unusual collaborations, be it rappers like Flohio or PS Hitsquad, solo artists like Mykki Blanco and Bobby Gillespie… So, we asked Adam if he'd like to work on a collaborative mix with us. He was well up for it and we all decided on one word as a guide, which was ""romance"". Half the selections on this mix are ours, half are his." - God Colony

When visionary electronic producer SOPHIE passed away in 2021 aged only 34, it felt like the extinguishing of a future path for music, the one down which she was lighting the way. Few musicians in 21st Century have diffused their influence throughout pop music and beyond as inexorably as SOPHIE. 
She created sounds that tore music – and by extension her own identity – down to its molecular constituents, alchemising them to thrilling effect, in a way that spellbound both the avant-garde and the poptimists alike. Since her passing, her devoted fanbase remains as active as ever, cataloging and archive SOPHIE's vast discography of officially and unofficially released music. 
Selected and mixed by Jennifer Walton.
